name: Overnight Oats with Soft-Cooked Egg and Miso-Braised Kale

steps.instruction:
Made by [Claire Saffitz](https://www.bonappetit.com/recipe/overnight-oats-with-soft-cooked-egg-and-miso-braised-kale)

### Prep
- Coarsely chop the kale
- Thinly Slice the Scallions

### Steps
1. Cook eggs in a medium saucepan of boiling water for 6 minutes
2. Immediately transfer to a bowl of ice water and let sit until cool, about 5 minutes
3. arefully peel eggs under running water (yolks will be partially set); set aside.

4. Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium
5. Add kale and cook, tossing, until wilted, about 2 minutes
6. Add mirin, soy sauce, miso, and ¼ cup water and stir until miso is dissolved
7. Bring to a simmer over low heat, partially cover, and cook until kale is tender, 5–10 minutes

8. Divide oats and yogurt among bowls, spooning yogurt into centers
9. Spoon kale mixture along with juices over yogurt, then place an egg on top
10. Season eggs with salt, then top with scallions and furikake. Drizzle with chili oil
